According to our results and at low current densities, deprotonation of the adsorbent (Eq. 15) is the rate-limiting step in the OER process. At higher current densities, the rate-determining step moves to the oxidative adsorption of water (Eq. 14) [54]. It must be mentioned that the production of radicals by sonolysis has to be considered but appears to be not relevant here and further studies are necessary. Exchange current density at high overpotential regions slightly increases at all the temperatures under our investigation in presence of ultrasound. By comparing the high overpotential region at different temperatures, we can see that j
